tweet_text: Maria was torn apart from her small children and family, and received inadequate medical care and poor treatment while in ICE custody. As co-chairs of the Women's Working Group on Immigration reform, we spoke with Maria's sister Izabel about this trauma.--https://t.co/Jv9v1l7AtZ
IBM_text: Maria was torn apart from her small children and family, and received inadequate medical care and poor treatment while in ICE custody.

tweet_text: Rosa fled gang violence for safety. She was detained by ICE. On a 23-hr transfer between facilities, food and restroom access was restricted. She fell ill, didn't get adequate medical attention and was later hospitalized. ICE only released her when the pregnancy became high-risk.
IBM_text: Rosa fled gang violence for safety.

tweet_text: Many mothers-to-be in ICE detention came to America to escape poverty, violence and even death in their homelands. In detention facilities, they often experience stress, trauma and inadequate medical care, which can endanger them and their unborn child. It's injustice in action.
IBM_text: Many mothers-to-be in ICE detention came to America to escape poverty, violence and even death in their homelands.

tweet_text: It should be easy to agree that pregnant women deserve dignity and comfort. In detention centers throughout our nation, that's not what these women get.----@RepRoybalAllard and I wrote about the inhumanity pregnant women are facing in ICE detention.--https://t.co/7IuIlkpO6n
IBM_text: It should be easy to agree that pregnant women deserve dignity and comfort.
